# Svelte/SvelteKit SEO File Rules

Apply this when changing route components, page loads, layout logic, or SEO utilities.

## Route Metadata

- Define route-level SEO in a centralized, typed shape (title, description, canonical, image, robots, schema).
- Normalize canonical URLs to one host/path format; remove tracking/query noise where appropriate.
- Keep metadata generation side-effect free and testable.

## SSR and Content Discoverability

- Ensure meaningful content is present in SSR output for indexable pages.
- Do not gate core page copy behind client-only fetch when data can be loaded server-side.
- Avoid hidden or delayed-render critical text that search engines need to index.

## Structured Data

- Use valid JSON-LD for applicable page types (Article, FAQPage, Organization, BreadcrumbList, etc.).
- Keep schema fields sourced from real page data; no placeholder values in production.
- Validate generated schema shape before shipping.

## Routing and Crawl Control

- Guard against duplicate route variants (trailing slash, locale alias, query-driven duplicates).
- Use explicit robots directives only where needed (draft/previews/private pages).
- Ensure `sitemap.xml` generation reflects canonical indexable routes only.

## Verification Checklist

- View page source and confirm title, description, canonical, and robots tags are present.
- Confirm OG/Twitter metadata appears on first render.
- Confirm schema script is valid JSON and matches visible content.
- Run lint/tests for changed modules and fix regressions before completion.
